{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-051__align-001", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-051", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 1, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "sentence", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 51.1", "chinese_text": "道生之，德畜之，物形之，勢成之。", "translation_ref": "老子 51.1", "translation_text": "All things are produced by the Dao, and nourished by its outflowing operation."}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-051__align-002", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-051", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 2, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "sentence", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 51.2", "chinese_text": "是以萬物莫不尊道而貴德。", "translation_ref": "老子 51.2", "translation_text": "They receive their forms according to the nature of each, and are completed according to the circumstances of their condition."}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-051__align-003", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-051", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 3, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "sentence", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 51.3", "chinese_text": "道之尊，德之貴，夫莫之命而常自然。", "translation_ref": "老子 51.3", "translation_text": "Therefore all things without exception honour the Dao, and exalt its outflowing operation."}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-051__align-004", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-051", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 4, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "sentence", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 51.4", "chinese_text": "故道生之，德畜之。長之育之，亭之毒之，蓋之覆之。", "translation_ref": "老子 51.4", "translation_text": "This honouring of the Dao and exalting of its operation is not the result of any ordination, but always a spontaneous tribute."}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-051__align-005", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-051", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 5, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "sentence", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 51.5", "chinese_text": "生而不有，為而不恃，", "translation_ref": "老子 51.5", "translation_text": "Thus it is that the Dao produces (all things), nourishes them, brings them to their full growth, nurses them, completes them, matures them, maintains them, and overspreads them."}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-051__align-006", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-051", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 6, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "sentence", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 51.6", "chinese_text": "長而不宰。是謂玄德。", "translation_ref": "老子 51.6", "translation_text": "It produces them and makes no claim to the possession of them; it carries them through their processes and does not vaunt its ability in doing so; it brings them to maturity and exercises no control over them; - this is called its mysterious operation."}
